description.narrative: (Uganda): .The HIV/Health Initiatives in Workplaces Activity (HIWA) aims to improve the health of employees of the Uganda Police Force (UPF), 11 Private Security Companies (PSC), Uganda's seven conservation areas under the Uganda Wildlife Authority (UWA) and 80 select hotels under the Uganda Hotel Owners Association (UHOA). Working in 54 districts across Uganda, HIWA reaches not only the target population of 111,624 employees of the selected occupational sectors, but also their family members and communities. With FY 2018 funds, HIWA will increase access to and uptake and use of quality maternal and child health, family planning, TB, nutrition, HIV/AIDS and WASH services. To reach this goal, HIWA will: strengthen provision of advanced quality and respectful reproductive, maternal, neonatal and child health (RMNCH) care in communities and at health facilities; create demand, increase access, and improve uptake of quality RMNCH services; increase access to rights-based, quality family planning services for all women, especially youth and low parity women; strengthen integration of the Nutrition, Assessment, Counseling and Support (NACS) interventions in the Feed the Future zone of influence by building health worker capacity and scaling-up high impact interventions; promote WASH services through adoption of "small doable actions" at health facilities and in communities to reduce morbidity in under five children; and scale-up gender based violence prevention and treatment... .
